> The extended methodological appendix, written **continuously** alongside the
> analysis. Governance: `.claude/policies/analysis/methods-documentation.md`.

## Statistical methods (journal style, extended)

Write the methods in fluent biostatistics-journal language (not code), at
appendix length, with LaTeX equations where needed. Use only notation declared in
`../docs/analysis/notation.md` (the `notation-check` hook enforces this). Example:

$$
\operatorname{logit}\,\Pr(Y_i = 1 \mid X_i) = \beta_0 + \beta_1 X_i .
$$

## Data processing (biomedical-informatics style)

A detailed account of processing: pseudocode (see `../docs/analysis/`), the
validation checks run (contracts, join cardinality, missingness/outlier
handling), and the iterations performed. Keep it reproducible and auditable.
